<paragraph id="A86536F5E078FF9C029BFF3B52E19E6A" blockId="12.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">
<materialsCitation id="18B23CA8E078FF9C029BFF3B52E49E6A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3091107313" collectorName="La Merced. This &amp; La Merced" country="Peru" county="Chanchamayo Province" location="Rio Chanchamayo. Although" municipality="Andes Mountains" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="Junin" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C029BFF3B506D9FFF" bold="true" box="[199,360,186,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Type locality:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="D0CD7665E078FF9C0333FF3B50A29FFE" box="[367,423,187,213]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingMunicipality id="4801AC8FE078FF9C03ECFF3B53289FFE" box="[432,557,187,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">La Merced</collectingMunicipality>
. This city is in 
<collectingCounty id="41044E79E078FF9C008FFF3B52D89FFE" box="[723,989,187,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Chanchamayo Province</collectingCounty>
in the 
<collectingRegion id="6A1EF817E078FF9C067BFF3B55BE9FFE" box="[1063,1211,187,213]" country="Peru" name="Junin" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Junín Region</collectingRegion>
on the eastern slope of the 
<collectingMunicipality id="4801AC8FE078FF9C0281FF5F50A39FD2" box="[221,422,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Andes Mountains</collectingMunicipality>
. The major river in 
<collectingMunicipality id="4801AC8FE078FF9C00DEFF5F53F89FD2" box="[642,765,223,249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">La Merced</collectingMunicipality>
is 
<location id="AD05602EE078FF9C0140FF5F55679FD2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:207387E3E07FFF9C02CBF8DF54729DAE:AD05602EE078FF9C0140FF5F55679FD2" box="[796,1122,223,249]" country="Peru" county="Chanchamayo Province" municipality="Andes Mountains" name="Rio Chanchamayo. Although" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" stateProvince="Junin">Río Chanchamayo. Although</location>
several tributaries flow into this river in the vicinity of 
<collectingMunicipality id="4801AC8FE078FF9C0394FE8353439E36" box="[456,582,259,285]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">La Merced</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<location id="AD05602EE078FF9C000EFE8352279E36" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:207387E3E07FFF9C02CBF8DF54729DAE:AD05602EE078FF9C000EFE8352279E36" box="[594,802,259,285]" country="Peru" county="Chanchamayo Province" municipality="Andes Mountains" name="Rio Chanchamayo" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" stateProvince="Junin">Río Chanchamayo</location>
has the habitat characteristics typical of species of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C0735FE8350009E6A" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C0735FE8350009E6A" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; thus, this likely is the stream from which the type was collected
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E0C0657EE078FF9C029BFECA54899EFA" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A86536F5E078FF9C029BFECA54899EFA" blockId="12.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C029BFECA504A9E4F" bold="true" box="[199,335,330,356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Discussion:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="77618857E078FF9C03DAFECB50ED9E4E" box="[390,488,331,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">holotype</typeStatus>
is a brachypterous male and its right hindleg is complete only through the trochanter, the left hindleg and both middle legs are complete only through the femora (
<figureCitation id="30E12A70E078FF9C01BCFEEF556C9EA2" box="[992,1129,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,959,983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,935]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1435,181,935]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Holotypes of (21) Cryphocricos obscuratus, dorsal, (22) Cryphocricos peruvianus, dorsal and (23) Cryphocricos peruvianus, ventral. Figure 23 courtesy of H.D.D. Rodrigues." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693096/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
). Glue to hold the specimen to the pin renders much of the mesosternum and middle leg bases obscured from view. The first record of a chironomid living phoretically on an aquatic bug was 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C00C3FE37550A9EFA" authority="Thienemann, 1926" authorityName="Thienemann" authorityYear="1926" box="[671,1039,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C00C3FE3752329EFA" box="[671,823,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Eukiefferiella</emphasis>
Thienemann, 1926
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C0665FE37548D9EFA" authority="(Roback 1977)" baseAuthorityName="Roback" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[1081,1416,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruvianus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C0665FE3755D39EFB" box="[1081,1238,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. peruvianus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E078FF9C06B9FE37547A9EFA" author="Roback, S. S." box="[1253,1407,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" pagination="192" refId="ref13674" refString="Roback, S. S. (1977) First record of a chironomid larva living phoretically on an aquatic hemipteran (Naucoridae). Entomological News, 88, 192." type="journal article" year="1977">Roback 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E0C0657EE078FF9C029BFE5A54729DAE" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A86536F5E078FF9C029BFE5A54729DAE" blockId="12.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C029BFE5A50419EDF" bold="true" box="[199,324,474,500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
In comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C0068FE5B53B59EDE" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[564,688,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C0068FE5B53B59EDE" box="[564,688,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is narrower, granulations (=tubercles) are more pronounced, and the posterolateral corners of the hemelytra very slightly rounded (
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E078FF9C0645FE7F55C09D32" author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[1049,1221,511,537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" pagination="426 - 433" refId="ref12276" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1940) I) Descripcion de tres especies nuevas del genero Cryphocricus Signoret. II). Una nueva especie del genero Heleocoris Stal (Hemiptera-Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 10, 426 - 433." type="journal article" year="1940">De Carlo 1940</bibRefCitation>
). In the key to brachypterous specimens, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E078FF9C03C0FDA353429D16" author="Usinger, R. L." box="[412,583,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" pagination="329 - 343" refId="ref14212" refString="Usinger, R. L. (1947) Classification of the Cryphocricinae (Hemiptera: Naucoridae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 40, 329 - 343. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 40.2.329" type="journal article" year="1947">Usinger (1947)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C00B7FDA3528D9D17" baseAuthorityName="Roback" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[747,904,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruvianus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C00B7FDA3528D9D17" box="[747,904,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. peruvianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C0192FDA355599D16" authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[974,1116,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daguerrei">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C0192FDA355599D16" box="[974,1116,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. daguerrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the evenly curved lateral margin of the abdomen, from 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C03BBFDC753479D4A" authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[487,578,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C03BBFDC753479D4A" box="[487,578,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C0024FDC753F29D4A" authorityName=": Usinger" authorityYear="1947" box="[632,759,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breddini">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C0024FDC753F29D4A" box="[632,759,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. breddini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the straight apical margins of the hemelytra, and from 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C07DFFDC751F59DAE" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C07DFFDC751F59DAE" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its larger size (&gt; 
<quantity id="6F229B10E078FF9C0393FDEB53279DAE" box="[463,546,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
). Note that 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E078FF9C00F8FDEB52A49DAE" authorityName=": Usinger" authorityYear="1947" box="[676,929,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breddini">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E078FF9C00F8FDEB52A49DAE" box="[676,929,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="84">Cryphocricos breddini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only by the macropterous form.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
